  "primitive": "sealed-poe-unwrap-negative",
  "source": "Structured-result and raise vectors over the wrap-n1-empty envelope, plus the hybrid behavioural negatives (garbage kem_ct of valid length, wrong-recipient seed over the honest envelope, and a sibling-slot kem_ct flip proving slots_mac covers every slot's KEM material). Includes the hashes-splice rejection (an honest envelope under a different item hashes map fails slots_mac), the per-slot KEK-reuse rejection (duplicate epk → ENC_SLOTS_DUPLICATE_KEM_MATERIAL), the header-binding nonce swap (the nonce salts every per-slot KEK, so no slot opens), and the exact-length raises for both sides of the hybrid kem_ct check.",
